Key Match Events: Max Fried pitched three-hit ball over 8 2/3 innings to lead the Atlanta Braves to a 3-0 victory over Kansas City
Sean Murphy hit a two-run homer
Marcell Ozuna scored on a throwing error after his first stolen base since 2022
Pre-Game Insights: The Mets were playing at Milwaukee, while the Diamondbacks hosted the Padres
Max Fried has spent his entire career with the Braves, but he’s set to become a free agent after the World Series
Royals' Vinnie Pasquantino was on the field during batting practice and will take simulated at-bats against reliever Will Smith on Saturday
Post-Match Reflections: Fried recognized the significance of the moment as he walked off the field to a huge cheer from the crowd at Truist Park
Braves' RHP Reynaldo López will make his first appearance since a start at Washington on Sept. 10
Miscellaneous Highlights: Royals' Brady Singer allowed two runs on four hits with three walks and five strikeouts
Braves' Max Fried threw 98 pitches, 63 for strikes
Braves' Sean Murphy homered on an 0-2 sweeper that caught the middle of the zone in the fourth
Braves' Marcell Ozuna stole third and scored on a throwing error by Royals' Salvador Perez
